<title type="html"><![CDATA[The Husband And Wife Who Never Disagreed For 20 Years On Even One Word]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="https://forum.salafiri.com/viewtopic.php?t=1377&amp;p=1461#p1461"><![CDATA[
<strong><span style="font-size: 200%; line-height: normal">The Husband And Wife Who Never Disagreed For 20 Years On Even One Word</span></strong><br /><br /><em>Abasa bint al Fadal the Wife of Imam Ahmad bin Hanbal</em><br /><br />Ibn Abi Yala said:<br />زوجة إمامنا أحمد وأم ابنه صالح كان أحمد يثني عليها وسمعت منه أشياء وماتت في حياته.<br /> قال زهير بن صالح بن أحمد تزوج جدي أم أبي عباسة بنت الفضل وهي من العرب من الربض ولم يولد له منها غير أبي ثم توفيت وقال أحمد أقامت أم صالح معي عشرين سنة فما اختلفت أنا وهي في كلمة.<br /><br />She was the wife of our Imam Ahmad and mother of his son Saaleh, Ahmad Praised her.. She died in his life.<br /><br />Zaheer bin Saaleh bin Ahmad said: my grandfather married The Mother of my Father Abbasa bint Fadal  who was from Arab.. she had no other children other than my father (Saaleh) until she died.<br /><br />Ahmad said: Umm Saleh stood with me for twenty years, and we <strong><span style="color: #0000FF">do not DISAGREE ON EVEN ONE WORD</span></strong>. [Tabqaat al Hanabilah (1/427), See also Tareekh Baghdad 14/438]<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="https://forum.salafiri.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=56">Shehzad Sattar</a> — Sat Mar 25, 2017 10:34 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
